The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, March 24 (PTI): India is set to have the second-largest wireless network in the world with a subscriber base of over 300 million by April, the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai) said today.          China has the worlds largest wireless network, adding around 6-7 million subscribers every month. The US, whose subscriber base is 256 million, adds about 2-3 million subscribers monthly whereas Indias monthly addition is the highest, in the range of 8-9 million, Trai said.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The government has assigned the Sashastra Seema Bal to protect volunteers of Salva Judum, the peoples movement against Naxalites in Chattisgarh, following a spate of attacks by Maoists. The decision came after intelligence inputs hinted at imminent Naxalite attacks.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The Mughal Gardens at the Rashtrapati Bhavan will be open exclusively for the blind on March 25 as a special treat.                   
	Coimbatore (PTI): A teacher has been suspended after she hit a boy on the head with a hardboard writing pad, police said on Monday. Though he was bleeding, the teacher forced him to complete the exam and told him not to inform his parents about the incident. The eight-year-old Class II student of a local private school needed five stitches to stop the bleeding. His father has lodged a complaint.                   
	Kanpur (PTI): A pregnant woman and her husband were shot dead by motorcycle-borne attackers near Govindnagar, police said. The couples love marriage seven months ago had allegedly angered the womans uncle who is a suspect in the murder. Three persons have been arrested and investigations are on. A search is on to nab the suspects including the uncle and his younger brother.                  
	 Nagpur (PTI): Police received a hoax call on Monday about a bomb in in the district court here. Nagpur police brought in sniffer dogs but found nothing.
                                                                                                                           
